{"word":"ἀροτήρ","slug":"ἀροτήρ","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀροτήρ</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἀρόω'><el>ἀρόω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>a plougher, husbandman</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>; <el>Σκύθαι ἀροτῆρες</el>, <a href='S:opposed to'>opp. to</a> <el>νομάδες</el>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>:—<a href='S:Adjective'>adj.</a>, <el>βοῦς ἀροτήρ</el> a steer <i>for ploughing</i>, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>a father</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}